name: quality
definition: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities.

comment: Should be defined using translocation.
name: mobility
definition: A quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to move freely.

name: speed
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's scalar absolute value of the rate of change of the bearer's position.

name: age
definition: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of how long the bearer has existed.

name: color
definition: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.

name: color hue
definition: A chromatic scalar-circular quality inhering in an object that manifests in an observer by virtue of the dominant wavelength of the visible light; may be subject to fiat divisions, typically into 7 or 8 spectra.

comment: Color brightness refers to the intensity, lightness or value of the light present. Think of this as a dimmer switch.
name: color brightness
definition: A scalar optical property that is the intensity, value or amount of perceived light.

comment: Color saturation refers to the amount of white light or gray paint mixed in with the hue (single wavelength) and is a measure of color purity.
name: color saturation
definition: A scalar chromatic property that is the degree of purity of perceived light.

name: fluorescence
definition: A luminous flux quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's emitting longer wavelength light following the absorption of shorter wavelength radiation; fluorescence is common with aromatic compounds with several rings joined together.

name: color pattern
definition: A chromatic property that is the relative position of different hues or degrees of saturation.

comment: Needs redefined or obsoleted. Is this the same as genetic incompatibility? Moved to organismal quality.
name: compatibility
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to harmonious coexistence.

name: composition
definition: A single physical entity inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's quantities or relative ratios of subparts.
comment: For example calcium composition (which may inhere in bone), haemoglobin composition (which may inhere in blood).

name: concentration of
definition: A quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the amount of the bearer's there is mixed with another substance.

name: consistency
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's density, firmness, or viscosity.

comment: TODO: consider merging with angular placement.
name: direction
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's orientation in space.

name: distance
definition: A quality that is the extent of space between two entities.

name: flavor
definition: A quality of a physical entity inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer's molecules are being perceived by a taste and odorant receptors.

name: frequency
definition: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the number of the bearer's repetitive actions in a particular time.

name: biological sex
definition: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to undergo sexual reproduction in order to differentiate the individuals or types involved.

name: hardness
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

name: intensity
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's possessing or displaying a distinctive feature in type or degree or effect or force.

name: life span
definition: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's expected maximum age.

name: morphology
definition: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

name: shape
definition: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ratios of distances between its features (points, edges, surfaces and also holes etc).
comment: Shapes are invariant on size transformations. Shapes can be subdivided into 2D and 3D shapes, We can also make a distinction between shapes of complete self-connected objects, and shapes of parts of objects.

name: trophic quality
definition: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to synthesize a particular organic compound required for its growth.

name: occurrence
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence.

name: odor
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's molecules being are aerially dispersed and perceived by an odorant receptor.

name: parental quality
definition: A parental quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of exhibiting the characteristic of a parent.

name: spatial pattern
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting repetition of placement of its parts.

name: sleep pattern
definition: A sleep quality defined by the mathematic properties of the relative time frames of the sleep cycle.

name: pilosity
definition: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having hair or bristles.

comment: TODO: define this or obsolete it and move children somewhere else.
name: qualitative
deviation(from_normal)
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer differs from normal or average.

name: count
definition: The number of entities of this type that are part of the whole organism.
comment: This term was originally named \"presence\". It has been renamed to reduce ambiguity. Consider annotating with the reciprocal relation,PATO:0001555, has_number_of. For example, rather than E=fin ray Q=count in organism C=10, say E=organism Q=has number of E2= fin ray C=10.

name: response to
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer's disposition to react to a stimulus or an agent.

name: rhythm quality
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's movement or variation characterized by the regular recurrence or alternation of different quantities or conditions.

name: amplitude
definition: A physical quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the size of the bearer's maximum displacement from the 'normal' position, when periodic motion is taking place.

name: persistence
definition: A rhythm quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the repetitiveness of bearer's rhythm.

name: phase
definition: A quality that exists by virtue of being a particular point in the time of a cycle.

name: sensitivity toward
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to detect or perceive external stimulation.

name: size
definition: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude.

name: height
definition: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's vertical dimension of extension.

name: length
definition: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.

name: mass
definition: A physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the proportion of the bearer's amount of matter.

name: weight
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer that has mass near a gravitational body.

name: orientation
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement which is defined by the angle between the bearer and an axis, or the angle between the bearer and another object.

name: closure
definition: A morphological quality pertaining to the degree to which an object contains an opening, aperture, orifice or vent.

name: position
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's spatial location relative to other objects in the vicinity.

name: structure
definition: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's relative position, shape, arrangements and connectivity of an organism's various parts; the pattern underlying its form.

comment: This term was made obsolete because it is not a quality. To update annotations, consider the following term 'quality of a solid; 'PATO:0001546'
name: solid substance

comment: This term was made obsolete because it is not a quality. To update annotations, consider the following term 'quality of a liquid; PATO:0001548 '
name: liquid substance
temperature
definition: A physical quality of the thermal energy of a system.

name: texture
definition: A morphologic quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's relative size, organization and distribution of its surface elements or the representation or invention of the appearance of its surface; visual and tactile surface characteristics.

name: threshold
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's sensitivity towards a fixed location or value where a change is observed; upper limit.

name: rate
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence per unit time.

name: time
definition: A quality in which events occur in sequence.

name: bouts
definition: A limited, often assigned period of activity.

name: viability
definition: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer or a population by virtue of the bearer's disposition to survive and develop normally or the number of surviving individuals in a given population.

name: balance
definition: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having physical steadiness.

name: behavioral quality
definition: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's behavior aggregate of the responses or reactions or movements in a given situation.

comment: Use GO:0007631 ! feeding behavior plus PATO instead.
name: consumption quality
definition: A relational quality of occurrent inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to consume a resource.

name: coordination
definition: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having or lacking skillful and effective interaction of movement.

name: discrimination
definition: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer's disposition to perceive differences between two or more stimuli.

name: maturity
definition: A quality of a single physical entity which is held by a bearer when the latter exhibits complete growth, differentiation, or development.

name: fecundity
definition: A reproductive quality inhering in an organism or population by virtue of the bearer's potential reproductive capacity ad measured by the number of gametes.

name: fertility
definition: A reproductive quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's initiating, sustaining, or supporting reproduction.

name: brood size
definition: A reproductive quality inhering in the young of an animal by virtue of their number.

name: female fertility
definition: A fertility quality inhering in a female by virtue of the bearer's disposition to initiate, sustain, or support reproduction.

name: male fertility
definition: A fertility quality of inhering in a male by virtue of the bearer's disposition to initiate, sustain, or support reproduction.

name: arrested
definition: A quality of a process which ends earlier than the natural end time or reference process.
comment: TODO: the definition is incorrect. See absent.

name: mobile
definition: A mobility quality of inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to move freely.

name: immobile
definition: A mobility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being incapable to move freely.

name: increased speed
definition: A speed which is relatively high.

name: decreased speed
definition: A speed which is relatively low.

name: old
definition: An age which is relatively high.

name: young
definition: An age which is relatively low.

name: black
definition: A color that lacks any hues as parts.

name: blue
definition: A color hue with low wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between green and indigo, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 420 to 490 nanometers.

name: cyan
definition: A color consisting of green and blue hue.

name: green
definition: A color hue with medium-low wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between yellow and blue, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 490 to 570 nanometers.

name: magenta
definition: A color consisting of red and blue hues.

name: red
definition: A color hue with high wavelength of the long-wave end of the visible spectrum, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 630 to 750 nanometers.

name: white
definition: An achromatic color of maximum brightness; the color of objects that reflect nearly all light of all visible wavelengths.

name: yellow
definition: A color hue with medium wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between orange and green, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 570 to 590 nanometers.

name: low brightness
definition: A color brightness which is relatively low.

name: low saturation
definition: A color saturation which is of low purity.

name: blotchy
definition: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer's being marked with irregularly shaped spots or blots of a different hue or degree of saturation.

name: irregular spatial pattern
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude of or the relationships between its repeated parts lack consistency.

name: discolored
definition: A color quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being altered or spoiled in color.

name: spotted
definition: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer's being marked with a round area of different hue or degree of saturation.

name: colored
definition: A color quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having color.

name: colorless
definition: A color quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking color.

name: compatible
definition: A compatibility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being capable of harmonious coexistence.

name: incompatible
definition: A compatibility quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being incapable of harmonious coexistence.

name: down
definition: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's direction from a higher to a lower point.

name: left
definition: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the north when it faces east.

name: right
definition: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's direction that is similar to the direction of an object to the north when it faces west.

name: up
definition: A directional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's direction from a lower to a higher point.

name: increased distance
definition: A distance which is greater relative to the normal or average.

name: decreased distance
definition: A distance which is lesser relative to the normal or average.

name: increased frequency
definition: A frequency which is relatively high.

name: decreased frequency
definition: A frequency which is relatively low.

name: female
definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population that only produces gametes that can be fertilised by male gametes.

name: male
definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population whose sex organs contain only male gametes.

name: hard
definition: A hardness quality of being rigid and resistant to pressure.

name: soft
definition: A hardness quality of giving little resistance to pressure.

name: acute
definition: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a sudden onset, sharp rise, and short course.

name: mild intensity
definition: An intensity which is less than moderate in type or degree or effect or force.

name: moderate intensity
definition: An intensity which is less than extreme in type or degree or effect or force.

name: severe intensity
definition: An intensity which is extremely bad or unpleasant in type or degree or effect or force.

name: branched
definition: A branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having branches.

name: cleft
definition: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a groove or fissure.

name: coiled
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curled or wound (especially in concentric rings or spirals).

name: curled
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having parallel chains in undulate fashion on the border.

name: curved
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having or being marked by a curve or smoothly rounded bend.

name: flat
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a horizontal surface without a slope, tilt, or curvature.

name: oblate
definition: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting an equatorial diameter greater than its polar diameter.

name: pinnate
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having leaflets or leaflets-like structures on each side of a common axis.

name: circular
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being such that every part of the surface or the circumference is equidistant from the center.

name: square
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an equal-sided rectangular form.

name: unbranched
definition: A branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking branches.

name: uncoiled
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being not curled or wound (especially in concentric rings or spirals).

name: auxotrophic
definition: A nutritional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's inability to synthesize a particular organic compound required for its growth.

name: prototrophic
definition: A nutritional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to synthesize a particular organic compound required for its growth.

name: recurrent
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurring or appearing again or repeatedly.

name: sporadic
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's once or in or a few unpredictable instances.

name: paternal
definition: A parental quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of exhibiting the characteristic of a father.

name: maternal
definition: A parental quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of exhibiting the characteristic of a mother.

name: invariant
definition: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking or not exhibiting variation.

name: regular spatial pattern
definition: A pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a repeatable or predictable placement.

name: repetitive
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's marked by tedious repetition.

comment: Consider NBO:0000422.
name: insomnia
definition: A sleep pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's inability to sleep.

comment: Consider NBO:0000423
name: narcolepsy
definition: A sleep pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disrupted sleep during normal sleeping period; often accompanied by cataplexy, sleep paralysis.

name: glabrous
definition: A pilosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lack of hairs or bristles.

name: hairy
definition: A pilosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being covered with hair or hairlike projections.

name: pubescent
definition: A maturity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having arrived at the onset of puberty (the age at which sex glands become functional) but not yet fully mature.

name: abnormal
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's deviation from normal or average.

name: normal
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting no deviation from normal or average.

name: absent
definition: A quality denoting the lack of an entity.
comment: Example: [ E=wing Q=absent ] -applies to an organism that lacks wings. Note that this is the reciprocal quality to the relational quality \"lacks all parts of type\". This means that [E=wing Q=absent] is replaceable with [E=organism Q=lacks_all_parts_of_type E2=Wing]. The latter is preferable as it allows greater precision in stating what is lacking from where. E.g. We can say [E=spermatocyte Q=lacks_all_parts_of_type E2=aster] to describe spermatocytes that have no asters.

name: conspicuous
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being clearly visible.

name: inconspicuous
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of not being clearly visible.

name: present
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's existence.

name: present in greater numbers in organism
definition: An amount which is relatively high.

name: responsive to
definition: A response quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to react to a stimulus or an agent.

name: unresponsive to
definition: A response quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lack of reaction to a stimulus or an agent.

name: increased duration
definition: A duration quality of a process which is relatively high.

name: decreased duration
definition: A duration quality of a process which is relatively low.

name: advanced phase
definition: A phase which occurs earlier than the natural start time.

name: dark phase
definition: A phase which occurs during dark cycle.

name: delayed
definition: A quality of a process which starts later than the natural start time or the reference process.

name: light phase
definition: A phase which occurs during the light cycle.

name: arrhythmic
definition: A rhythm quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking rhythm.

name: rhythmic
definition: A rhythm quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having rhythm.

name: insensitive toward
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking sensitivity toward an external stimulus.

name: tolerant to
definition: A resistance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its disposition to endure or being insensitive to a stimulus.

name: sensitive toward
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having sensitivity toward an external stimulus.

name: photoinsensitive
definition: A photosensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking photosensitivity.

name: photosensitive
definition: A photosensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting photosensitivity.

name: decreased height
definition: A height which is relatively low.

name: increased height
definition: A height which is relatively high.

name: increased length
definition: A length quality which is relatively large.

name: decreased length
definition: A length quality which is relatively small.

name: increased weight
definition: A weight which is relatively high.

name: decreased weight
definition: A weight which is relatively low.

name: hypertrophic
definition: An increased size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting enlargement of a cell or constituent group of cells (for example, organ).

name: hypotrophic
definition: A decreased size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting reduced size of a cell or constituent group of cells (for example, organ).

name: increased size
definition: A size quality which is relatively high.

name: decreased size
definition: A size quality which is relatively low.

name: vestigial
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being a remnant structure from earlier development or evolution.

name: increased thickness
definition: A thickness which is relatively high.

name: decreased thickness
definition: A thickness which is relatively low.

name: increased volume
definition: A volume which is relatively high.

name: decreased volume
definition: A volume which is relatively low.

name: decreased width
definition: A width which is relatively small.

name: increased width
definition: A width which is relatively large.

name: closed
definition: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's affording blocked passage or view.

name: closure incomplete
definition: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's affording not completed blocked passage or view.

name: open
definition: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's affording unobstructed passage or view.

name: disoriented
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking orientation.

name: oriented
definition: A pattern where all the repeated elements are oriented in the same direction.

name: anterioralized
definition: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing only what are normally anterior structures.

name: asymmetrical
definition: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking symmetry.

name: bent
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having one or more angle(s) in its length.

name: bilateral
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having two sides; two-sided.

name: crowded
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being overfilled.

name: dorsalized
definition: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing only what are normally dorsal structures.

name: erect
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being upright in position or posture.

name: exserted
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's protruding or projecting from the body.

name: inserted into
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's becoming joined together with an additional entity.

name: inverted
definition: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being reversed in position, order, or condition.

name: lateralized
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being moved or displaced to one side so as to make lateral.

name: localized
definition: A spatial pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being confined or restricted to a particular location.

name: mislocalised
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer's being changed in abnormal position.

name: misrouted
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having mistakenly taken course, way, or passage; ill-routed.

name: posterioralized
definition: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing only what are normally posterior structures.

name: prostrate
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being stretched out and lying at full length along the ground.

name: symmetrical
definition: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being capable of division by a longitudinal plane into similar halves.

name: uncrowded
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being not overfilled.

name: unilateral
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's involvement of only one part or side.

name: unlocalised
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not being confined or restricted to a particular location.

name: ventralized
definition: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gross morphology containing only what are normally ventral structures.

name: apoptotic

name: degenerate

name: dysplastic

name: fused with
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being merged with another entity.

name: herniated

name: necrotic

name: obstructed

name: unfused from

name: high brightness

name: continuous

name: discontinuous
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by breaks or interruptions.

name: heterochronic
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's origin or development at an unusual time or out of the regular sequence.

name: premature
definition: A quality of a process which starts earlier than the natural start time or the reference process.

name: synchronous
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurring or existing at the same time or having the same period or phase.

name: rough
definition: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's irregular surface.

name: smooth
definition: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's processing a surface free of roughness or irregularities.

name: increased threshold
definition: A threshold which is relatively high.

name: decreased threshold
definition: A threshold which is relatively low.

definition: A viability quality inhering in a population by virtue of the bearer's long term survival inability.

name: viable

name: balanced
definition: A balance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having balance.

definition: A balance quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking balance.

definition: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting paralytic behaviour when subjected to mechanical shock.

name: increased behavioural activity
definition: A behavioral quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting increased activity.

name: decreased behavioural activity
definition: A behavioral quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting reduced activity.

name: passive

name: euploid
definition: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing an integral multiple of the monoploid number, possibly excluding the sex-determining chromosomes.

comment: The exact number may be one or two different from the 2n number and still be classified as diploidy (although with aneuploidy). Nearly all mammals are diploid organisms, although all individuals have some small fracton of cells that are polyploidy.
name: diploid
definition: A ploidy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having two copies (homologs) of each chromosome, usually one from the mother and one from the father.

name: haplodiploid
definition: A diploidy quality inhering in a bearer in by virtue of belonging in a species whose one of the sexes has haploid cells and the other has diploid cells.

name: cellular quality
definition: A monadic quality of continuant that exists at the cellular level of organisation.

name: cellular potency
definition: A cellular quality that arises by virtue of whether the bearer's disposition to differentiate into one or more mature cell types.

name: self-renewal
definition: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having the ability to go through numerous cycles of cell division while maintaining the undifferentiated state.

name: totipotent
definition: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce differentiated cell types of all three primary germ layers and extraembryonic cell types.

comment: Unipotent cells have the quality of self-renewal which distinguishes them from non-stem cells.
name: unipotent
definition: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce only one differentiated cell type.

comment: Less potent than multipotent, often thought of as precursor or progenitor cell status.
name: oligopotent
definition: A cellular potency that is the capacity to form multiple differentiated cell types of a specific lineage and lack self renewing capacity.

name: multipotent
definition: A cellular potency that is the capacity to form multiple differentiated cell types.

name: pluripotent
definition: A cellular potency that is the capacity to produce differentiated cell types of all three primary germ layers but not extraembryonic cell types.

name: nucleate quality
definition: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer's number of nuclei.

name: anucleate
definition: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having no nucleus.

name: binucleate
definition: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having two nuclei.

name: mononucleate
definition: A nucleate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having one nucleus.

name: ciliatedness
definition: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having thin, tail-like projections extending outwards from the cell body.

name: spindle-shaped
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a long tapered rod.

name: striated
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by narrow lines or grooves, usually parallel.

name: structured
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having distinct structure.

name: unstructured
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking distinct structure.

name: angular velocity
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the rate of the bearer's angular movement about an axis; the angle rotated in a given time.

name: catalytic activity
definition: A physical quality inhering in a catalyst by virtue of the amount of the catalyst's action.

name: morbidity
definition: A quality inhering in a population by virtue of the proportion of its members that are ill at a given time.

name: regular duration
definition: A duration which has regular start and/or end times.

name: irregular duration
definition: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's duration which has irregular start and/or end times.

name: lethargic
definition: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being deficient in alertness or activity.

name: sharp
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's terminating in a point or edge.

name: buoyancy
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to rise or float in a fluid medium such as water or air.

name: alive
definition: A viability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's condition before death.

name: dead
definition: A viability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the cessation of the bearer's life.

name: refractile
definition: A reflectivity quality inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to refract light.

name: violet
definition: A color hue with very low wavelength of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between reddish blue or bluish purple, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 420 to 380 nanometers.

name: rosy
definition: A color hue consisting of red hue and yellow hue and high brightness.

name: maroon
definition: A color consisting of purple and brown hue.

name: compound acidity
definition: A concentration quality inhering in compound by virtue of the bearer's tendency to act as a hydron donor.

name: medium acidity
definition: A concentration quality inhering in a medium by virtue of the bearer's tendency to hydronate a specific reference base.

name: acidic
definition: An medium acidity quality inhering in a solution by virtue of the bearer's a high concentration of H+ ions.

name: alkaline
definition: An medium acidity quality inhering in a solution by virtue of the bearer's a low concentration of H+ ions.

comment: The definition is general enough to cover adhesion arising from different kinds of chemical bonding/forces, although for PATO this term will most commonly used for cellular adhesion. See also GO:0031589 \"cell-substrate adhesion\".
name: adhesivity
definition: An emergent molecular quality that arises by virtue of the bearer's disposition to exhibit molecular attraction to another entity in contact.

name: decayed
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's decomposition into component parts.

name: growth quality of occurrent
definition: A quality of a single process which describes the growth of an organism, structure, or group of organisms.

name: reproductive quality
definition: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to produce new life or offspring.

name: attachment quality
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having connection or association with another entity.

name: sessile (sensu botany)
definition: An attachment quality inhering in a flower by virtue of the bearer's lacking a stalk, as in flowers or leaves that grow directly from the stem.

name: sessile (sensu zoology)
definition: A attachment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's inability to move about.

name: pedicellate
definition: A attachment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having or being supported by a pedicel or pedicle.

name: tonicity
definition: A contractile quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's elastic tension that facilitate response to stimuli.
comment: TODO: we need a clearer differentium between this and contractility - or merge?

name: homophilic
definition: A cellular adhesivity quality inhering in a molecule in one cell by virtue of the bearer's attachment to an identical molecule in an adjacent cell.

name: heterophilic
definition: A cellular adhesivity quality inhering in a molecule in one cell by virtue of the bearer's attachment to an nonidentical molecule in an adjacent cell.

name: wholeness
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer includes all its components.

name: broken
definition: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being broken open.

name: disassembled
definition: A wholeness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being taken apart into its constituent parts.

name: whole
definition: A wholeness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's including all its components.

name: calcified
definition: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's being encrusted or impregnated with calcium carbonate (CHEBI:3311).

name: ossified
definition: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's being hardened by the deposition of calcium into bone.

comment: Cartilage is a type of dense connective tissue. It is composed of specialized cells called chondrocytes (CL:0000138) that produce a large amount of extracellular matrix composed of collagen fibers, abundant ground substance rich in proteoglycan, and elastin fibers.
name: cartilaginous
definition: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's cartilage quantities.

name: edematous
definition: A structural quality which is held by a bearer when the latter exhibits an excessive accumulation of extracellular fluid.

name: edematous (sensu botany)
definition: An extended swelling in plant organs caused primarily by an excessive accumulation of water.

name: detached from
definition: An attachment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking connection or association with another entity.

name: sensitivity to oxygen
definition: A sensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's dependence on oxygen.

name: aerobic
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's dependence on oxygen.

name: anaerobic
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's independence on oxygen.

name: sensitivity of a process
definition: A quality of a process inhering in bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to respond to stimulation.

name: sensitivity of a process to oxygen
definition: A sensitivity of a process quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's unfolding in a location with or without oxygen.

name: aerobic (for occurrence)
definition: A sensitivity of a process inhering in a biological process by virtue of the process unfolding in a location with oxygen.

name: anaerobic (for occurrence)
definition: A sensitivity of a process inhering in a biological process by virtue of the process unfolding in a location without oxygen.

name: surface tension
definition: A physical quality inhering in a liquid by virtue of the bearer's ability to attraction of molecules at its surface as a result of unbalanced molecular cohesive forces.

name: membrane potential
definition: A quality inhering in a cell's plasma membrane by virtue of the electrical potential difference across it.

name: action potential
definition: A quality inhering in a cell's plasma membrane by virtue of a brief fluctuation in the bearer's potential caused by the rapid opening and closing of voltage-gated ion channels.

name: electric potential
definition: A quality that is equal to the potential energy per unit charge associated with a static (time-invariant) electric field, also called the electrostatic potential.

name: monstrous
definition: A malformed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's all-encompassing, grotesque morphological defects.

name: curved rostral
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved towards the front of an organism.

name: curved caudal
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved towards the part of the body from which the tail arises.

name: curved dorsal
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved towards the back or upper surface of an organism.

name: curved ventral
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved towards the abdomen of an organism.

comment: Examples: height to weight; brain size to body size. These could all be children of proportionality. Proportions can be measured as ratios. Some measures may be dimensionless. Not all ratios measure proportionality, eg m/s measures velocity which is not a proportion in the sense defined above, it is a quality in its own right.
name: proportionality to
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude in respect to a related entity.

name: decreased depth
definition: A depth which is relatively low.

name: duplicated
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being present in two copies.

name: anteverted
definition: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's axis being positioned forward.

name: increased position
definition: A position which is relatively high.

name: decreased position
definition: A positional which is relatively low.

name: retracted
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being drawn in or pulled back from any given point.

name: collapsed
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being broken down; caved in.

name: spongy
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a sponge in elasticity, absorbency, or porousness.

name: sloped
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an oblique or slanted direction.

name: prominent
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's standing out or projecting beyond a surface or line.

name: aplastic
definition: A size quality inhering in a an organ or tissue by virtue of the bearer's absence coupled with persistence of the organ/tissue primordium, which fails to develop completely.

name: recent
definition: A quality of a process which occurs near to or not long before the present.

name: condensed
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being thicker or more closely packed together; pressed tightly together.

name: chronological age
definition: An age quality that exists by virtue of the time (years and months) that the bearer has existed.

name: senescent
definition: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's growing old; aging.

comment: Term should be obsoleted and the GO term cellular motility should be used instead.
name: cellular motility
definition: A cellular quality inhering in a cell by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability to move spontaneously.

name: heterochronic growth
definition: A growth quality of a process inhering in an organism, structure, or group of organisms by virtue of the bearer's reduced or increased growth.

name: neotenous growth
definition: A paedomorphic growth quality which is due to a reduced rate.

comment: This term will be obsoleted; Use GO:growth and PATO:rate.
name: growth rate

comment: This term will be obsoleted; Use GO:growth and PATO:rate.
name: hypertrophic growth

comment: This term will be obsoleted; Use GO:growth and PATO:rate.
name: hypotrophic growth
notched
definition: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's shape being a V-shaped cut.

name: brood quality
definition: A reproductive quality inhering in the young of an animal by virtue of the bearer's being cared for at one time.

name: brood viability
definition: A reproductive quality inhering in the young of an animal by virtue of the bearer's disposition to survive and develop normally.

name: spherical
definition: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a ball (a sphere whose equatorial diameter is equal to the polar diameter).

name: tapered
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being gradually narrower or thinner toward one end.

name: immature
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking complete growth, differentiation, or development.

comment: TODO: obsolete this.
name: complexity
definition: A monadic quality of continuant inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being intricate and compounded.

name: simple
definition: A complexity quality in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having few parts or being complicated or compound.

name: complex
definition: A complexity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being intricate and compounded.

name: separated from
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not being in contact with another entity, or of no longer being connected or joined with another entity.

name: diastatic
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's separation of normally joined parts, such as the separation of adjacent bones without fracture or of certain abdominal muscles during pregnancy.

name: disrupted
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being interrupted of its normal course.

name: functionality
definition: A quality of a single physical entity that arises by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability to perform a regular function(s).

name: functional
definition: A functionality quality held by the bearer when the latter is able to perform a regular function(s).

name: non-functional
definition: A disfunctional quality held by the bearer when the latter is unable to perform a regular function(s).

name: punctate
definition: A pattern inhering in a surface by virtue of the bearer's being marked by the presence of dots, punctures, points or pits.

name: delaminated
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking some outer layer.

name: variable color
definition: A color quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being uneven in color.

name: focus
definition: An optical quality where light rays originating from a point on the object converge.

name: focused
definition: An optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having focus.

name: blurry
definition: An optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking focus.

name: sound quality
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of vibration, as perceived by the sense of hearing.

name: sound frequency
definition: The frequency of transmitted vibrations.

name: sound amplitude
definition: A physical quality inhering in a sound wave by virtue of the maximum magnitude (value without regard to sign) of its disturbance.

name: sound speed
definition: A physical quality inhering in sound by virtue of the bearer's travelling speed in a given medium under specified conditions.

name: sound wavelength
definition: A physical quality which is equal to the quotient of the speed of a sound wave divided by its wavelength.

name: intrasonic
definition: A sound frequency in the range of 0-20 Hz.

name: sonic
definition: A sound frequency in the range of 20 to 20.000 Hz.

name: ultrasonic
definition: A sound frequency in the range of 20 000 + Hz.

name: quiet
definition: A sound amplitude which is relatively low.

name: loud
definition: A sound amplitude which is relatively high.

name: cellular spatiotemporal quality
definition: A spatiotemporal quality inhering in a cell.

name: behavioral quality of a process
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's behavior.

name: cellular adhesivity
definition: A cellular quality that exists by virtue of the disposition of the cell to adhere to other cells and molecules, through the emergent action of the molecular parts of the cell surface.

name: mono-colored
definition: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having one hue.

name: multi-colored
definition: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer's having two or more hues or degrees of saturation.

name: motley
definition: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer's having 3 or more hues or degrees of saturations.

name: dappled
definition: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer's being marked with small spots, patches, or specks of hue or degree of saturation differing from that of the background.

name: solubility
definition: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the bearer's disposition to dissolve in a liquid.

name: soluble in
definition: A solubility quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the bearer's disposition to dissolve in a liquid.

name: insoluble in
definition: A solubility quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the bearer's inability of a substance to dissolve in a liquid.

name: amylose composition
definition: A compositional quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's quantities or relative ratios of amylose of the inhering entity.

name: glutinous
definition: An amylose composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's having negligible or no amylose content.

name: non-glutinous
definition: An amylose composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's having high amount of amylose content.

name: delayed phase
definition: A phase which starts later than natural start point.

name: flexibility
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

name: flexible
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability of being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

name: inflexible
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's inability of being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

name: quality of a solid
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity characterized by particles arranged such that their shape and volume are relatively stable.

name: quality of a gas
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of particles that have neither a defined volume nor defined shape.

name: quality of a liquid
definition: A physical quality inhering in an entity exhibiting the physical characteristics of an amorphous (non-crystalline) form of matter between a gas and a solid that has a definite volume, but no definite shape.

name: increased sensitivity toward
definition: A sensitivity toward an external stimulus which is higher than normal/average.

name: decreased sensitivity toward
definition: A sensitivity toward an external stimulus which is lower than normal/average.

name: increased sensitivity of a process
definition: A sensitivity of a process which is higher than normal or average.

name: decreased sensitivity of a process
definition: A sensitivity of a process which is lower than normal or average.

synonyms.definition: high sensitivity of occurrent to oxygen

name: increased sensitivity of a process to oxygen
definition: A sensitivity of occurrent to oxygen which is higher than normal or average.

synonyms.definition: low sensitivity of occurrent to oxygen

name: decreased sensitivity of a process to oxygen
definition: A sensitivity of a process to oxygen which is lower than normal or average.

has or lacks parts of type

name: has number of
definition: The number of parts of a particular type that the bearer entity has. This is a relational quality, and thus holds between two entities: the bearer of the quality, and the type of parts.

name: lacking processual parts
definition: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking a processual part as specified by the additional entity.

name: having extra function
definition: A functionality quality which is held by the bearer when the latter is able to perform additional or different function(s).

name: having extra processual parts
definition: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having additional processual parts.

name: decreased mass
definition: A mass which is lower than normal or average.

name: increased mass
definition: A mass which is higher than normal or average.

name: extra or missing processual parts
definition: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's processual parts.

name: distributed
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being spread out or scattered about or divided up.

name: undistributed
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not being spread out or scattered about or divided up.

name: having decreased processual parts
definition: A quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having fewer processual parts.

name: dilated
definition: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being made wider or larger in all dimensions.

name: isometrical
definition: A symmetry quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having equal dimensions or measurements.

name: flow rate
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's motion characteristic.

name: decreased pressure
definition: A pressure which is relatively low.

name: increased pressure
definition: A pressure which is relatively high.

name: increased permeability
definition: A permeability which is relatively high.

name: decreased permeability
definition: A permeability which is relatively low.

name: contractility
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to shrink or contract.

name: increased contractility
definition: A contractility which is relatively high.

name: decreased contractility
definition: A contractility which is relatively low.

comment: GO has now relevant relation terms which should be used instead.
name: relaxational quality
definition: A spatial quality inhering in an inactive muscle or muscle fibers by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting gradual lengthening.

name: decreased variability
definition: A variability which is relatively low.

name: increased variability
definition: A variability which is relatively high.

comment: Examples could be heat or electricity or sound.
name: conductivity
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to transmit of an entity through a medium.

name: variability of rate
definition: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits rate variation or change.

name: increased variability of rate
definition: A variability of rate which is relatively high.

name: decreased variability of rate
definition: A variability of rate which is relatively low.

comment: Obsoleted because it used to be a child of behavioral quality, which really meant increased magnitude of a given behavior. Now this can be done by using increased magnitude with another quality.
name: enhanced
definition: Increased, intensified.

name: overlap with
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's coinciding spatially, partially or wholly with another entity.

name: curvature
definition: A surface shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a degree of bending.

name: increased curvature
definition: A curvature which is relatively high.

name: decreased curvature
definition: A curvature which is relatively low.

name: arched
definition: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's forming or resembling an arch.

name: depth
definition: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's downward or backward or inward dimenision.

name: increased depth
definition: A depth quality which is relatively high.

name: everted
definition: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being turned outward in placement.

name: protruding
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's extending out above or beyond a surface or boundary.

name: rotated
definition: An oriented quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being relocated around an axis.

name: posteriorly rotated
definition: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the rear of organism.

name: anteriorly rotated
definition: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the front of an organism.

name: distended
definition: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being abnormally expanded or increased in size.

name: increased life span
definition: A life span which is relatively high.

name: decreased life span
definition: A life span which is relatively low.

name: disheveled
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being in disarray; extremely disorderly.

name: greasy
definition: A coating which is oily and slippery.

name: matted
definition: A tangled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being not possible to unravel.

name: patchy
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by, consisting of, or diversified with patches.

name: sparse
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being scattered; spread irregularly, and at a distance from each other.

name: variability of color
definition: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits color variation or change.

name: increased variability of color
definition: A variability of color which is relatively high.

name: decreased variability of color
definition: A variability of color which is relatively low.

name: invariant color
definition: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking or not exhibiting variation of color.

name: variant color
definition: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having or exhibiting variation of colour.

name: deformed
definition: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being distorted in form.

name: increased tonicity
definition: A tonicity which is relatively high.

name: decreased tonicity
definition: A tonicity which is relatively low.

name: turgor
definition: A structural quality inhering in a cell or blood vessel or capillary by virtue of the bearer's being in a rigid state of fullness resulting from pressure of the contents against the wall or membrane.

name: decreased turgor
definition: A turgor which is relatively low.

name: increased turgor
definition: A turgor which is relatively high.

name: atrophied
definition: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of a part or parts of the bearer's being decreased in size due to reduction in tissue mass through wasting.

name: decreased functionality
definition: A functionality quality held by the bearer when the latter exhibits decreased ability to perform a regular function(s).

name: increased functionality
definition: A functional quality held by the bearer when the latter exhibits increased ability to perform a regular function(s).

name: sufficiency
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer has enough functionality.

name: sufficient
definition: A wholeness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's has enough functionality.

name: insufficient
definition: A wholeness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacks enough functionality.

name: aggregated
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being gathered or tending to gather into a mass or whole.

name: dispersed
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being distributed or spread over a considerable extent.

name: anterior to
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located toward the front of an organism relative to another entity.

name: posterior to
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located toward the rear of an organism relative to another entity.

name: necessity (continuant)
definition: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer is essential or indispensable.

name: necessary (continuant)
definition: A necessity quality (continuant) inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being essential or indispensable.

name: unnecessary (continuant)
definition: A necessity quality (continuant) inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being non-essential or dispensable.

name: necessity of occurrent
definition: A quality of single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer is essential or indispensable.

name: necessary (occurrent)
definition: A necessity quality inhering in a process by virtue of the bearer's being essential or indispensable.

name: unnecessary (occurrent)
definition: A necessity quality inhering in a process by virtue of the bearer's being non-essential or dispensable.

name: stubby
definition: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a short, stocky build.

name: protruding into
definition: A quality inhering into a bearer by virtue of the bearer's extending out above or beyond its surface or boundary into the surface or boundary of another entity.

name: protruding out of
definition: A quality inhering into a bearer by virtue of the bearer's extending out above or beyond its surface or boundary and outwards in relation to the physical space occupied by another entity.

name: circumference
definition: An 1-D extent quality which is equal to the length of the closed curve of a circle.

name: curved lateral
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved towards the side.

name: increased resistance to
definition: A resistance to a stimulus which is relatively high.

name: decreased resistance to
