definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being positioned towards the rear of an organism.

name: mislocalised laterally
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being positioned towards the side of an organism.

name: mislocalised medially
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being positioned towards the middle of an organism.

comment: This quality either inheres directly in the surface, or in the entity that has the surface. For example, to say that a particular fly wing is curved is shorthand for saying the wing has a surface which is curved.
name: surface feature shape
definition: A surface shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's shape of features present on its surface or outer shell.

name: increased fluorescence
definition: A fluorescence which is higher than normal.

name: decreased fluorescence
definition: A fluorescence which is lower than normal.

name: blistered
definition: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of a local accumulation of fluid underneath the surface of the bearer.

name: variability of shape
definition: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits shape variation or change.

name: variant shape
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer's having or exhibiting variation its shape.

name: invariant shape
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking or not exhibiting variation of shape.

name: alternate placement
definition: A pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being placed alternately one above the other.

name: opposite
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being positioned on opposite sides on the same plane.

name: orbicular
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being perfectly circular.

name: obtuse
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being roundish, a little inclining to be oblong.

name: obovate
definition: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being egg-shaped and flat, with the narrow end attached to the base.

name: spatulate
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being oblong, with the lower end very much attenuated.

name: rhomboid
definition: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being oval and a little angular in the middle.

name: gigantic
definition: A size quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being many folds greater relative to the normal average.

name: yellow green
definition: A color consisting of yellow and green hues.

name: brown green
definition: A color consisting of brown and green hues.

name: lilac
definition: A purple color which has low saturation and low brightness.

name: yellow orange
definition: A color consisting of yellow and orange hue.

name: ochre
definition: A moderate yellow-orange to orange color.

name: banded
definition: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer's exhibiting transverse stripes of one hue or degree of saturation crossing another.

name: netted
definition: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer's being covered with reticulated lines of a different hue or degree of saturation.

name: furrowed
definition: A grooved texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by two or more parallel channels.

name: pointleted
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's terminating abruptly in a little point.

name: blunt
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's terminating gradually in a rounded end.

name: whorled
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being in opposition round a common axis.

name: distichous
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being arranged in two opposite rows (and hence in the same plane).

name: decussate
definition: A pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting of paired parts that alternately cross each other.

name: subulate
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being linear, very narrow, tapering to a very fine point from a narrow base.

name: cuneate
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being narrowly triangular, wider at the apex and tapering toward the base.

name: variability of size
definition: A variability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits size variation or change.

name: decreased variability of size
definition: A variability of size which is relatively low.

name: increased variability of size
definition: A variability of size which is relatively high.

name: defasciculated
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's in which bundles of aligned anatomical fibers have become separated.

name: interdigitated
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's parts or projections being interlocked; for example, the fingers of two hands that are clasped.

name: in contact with
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's touching another entity.

name: involute
definition: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's edges of its surface being rolled inwards spirally on each side.

name: revolute
definition: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's edges of its surface being rolled backwards spirally on each side.

name: circinate
definition: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's edges of its surface being rolled spirally downwards.

name: reclinate
definition: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's edges of its surface being bent down upon their stalk.

name: convolute
definition: A curled quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's one edge of its surface being wholly rolled up in another.

name: actinodromous
definition: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having three or more primary branches diverging radially from a single point.

name: parallelodromous
definition: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having two or more parallel primary branches originate beside each other and converge apically.

name: craspedodromous
definition: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having secondary branches terminating at the margin.

name: brochidodromous
definition: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having secondary branches joined together in a series of prominent arches.

name: cladodromous
definition: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having secondary branches freely branching toward the margin.

name: reticulodromous
definition: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having secondary branches branching into a reticulum toward the margin.

name: cuspidate
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being tapering gradually into a rigid point.

name: retuse
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's terminating in a round end, the centre of which is depressed.

name: unserrated
definition: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking sharp straight-edged teeth pointing to the apex.

name: serration
definition: A surface feature shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having or lacking sharp straight-edged teeth pointing to the apex.

name: angular
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having at least one salient angle on the margin.

name: cut
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being regularly divided by deep incisions.

name: lobed
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being partly divided into a determinate number of regions.

name: digitate
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having distinct parts arising from a common point or center.

name: auriculate
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a shape resembling an ear.

name: attenuate
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's gradually tapering to a slender point.

name: perfoliate
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's two basal lobes being united together.

name: decurrent
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being prolonged below the point of insertion.

name: frozen
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being kept below its freezing point.

name: dissolved
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's passing into solution.

name: saccular
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a three dimensional cavity with a narrow or no opening, and often containing an anatomical substance.

name: quadrangular
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having four angles and four sides.

name: sinuous
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having many curves and turns.

comment: MAH: I think this term should be obsoleted. Is it used?
name: duration of disease
definition: A duration quality of a process inhering in a disease by virtue of the bearer's duration of an impairment of health or of a condition of abnormal functioning.

name: immortal
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being capable of indefinite growth or division.

name: cellularity
definition: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting cells.

name: multicellular
definition: A cellularity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting of more than one cell.

name: unicellular
definition: A cellularity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting of exactly one cell.

name: organismal quality
definition: A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.

name: present in fewer numbers in organism
definition: An amount which is relatively low.

comment: This term was created as a grouping term for the 2 terms \"conspicuous\" and \"inconspicuous\". However, it is not clear if these terms should even remain in PATO.
name: conspicuousness
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its visibility.

name: lacks parts or has fewer parts of type
definition: The bearer of this quality has_part < n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e has fewer parts of type X at time t, then the number of instances x of X at t such that x part_of e is < n, where n is either the normal number for comparable entities, or n is stated explicitly. This case includes the limit case, where the bearer lacks all parts of the specified type.

name: lacks all parts of type
definition: A quality of physical entities inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking a physical part as specified by the additional entity.
comment: Example: [E=organism Q=lacks_all_parts_of_type E2=Wing] - applies to an organism. A relational quality in which the bearer entity has no parts of the specified type. The bearer of this quality has_part = 0 of the indicated entity type, where a comparable organism usually has at least 1 part of the same type. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e lacks all parts of type X at time t, then there exists no instances x of X at t such that x part_of e that has no wings, where wings are normally present in that organism type. In OWL this is equivalent to a restriction on the OBO_REL:has_part relation with cardinality=0, i.e has_part 0 E2.

synonyms.definition: lacks all physical parts of type

name: has fewer parts of type
definition: The bearer of this quality has_part < n AND has_part > 0 of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part. Formally: If a bearer entity e has fewer parts of type X at time t, then the number of instances x of X at t such that x part_of e is < n, where n is either the normal number for comparable entities, or n is stated explicitly.
comment: Example: [E=hand Q=has_fewer_parts_of_type E2=digit] - applies to an organism that has no less fingers than is normal for organisms of that type.

synonyms.definition: has fewer physical parts of type

name: has extra parts of type
definition: The bearer of this quality has_part > n of the indicated entity type, where n is the normal amount for a comparable organism. Note that the bearer of the quality is the whole, not the part.
comment: In polydactyly, the bearer of the quality is the hand, and the entity type being counted is 'finger'. In EQ syntax, E=hand, Q=<this> E2=finger.

name: population quality
definition: A quality that inheres in an entire population or part of a population.

comment: Consider PATO:0001925 ! surface feature share
name: surface shape
definition: A shape that inheres in a part of a surface. An object can have different surface shapes on different parts of its surface.

name: concavity
definition: Surface shape that refers to the inward or outward curvature of the surface.

name: 2-D shape
definition: A shape that inheres in a 2 dimensional entity, such as a cross section or projection of a 3 dimensional entity.

name: convex 3-D shape
definition: A complete three dimensional shape in which for every line connecting pair of points on the object is within the object. Or: a shape lacking cavities. Contrast: concave.
comment: Use this term or an is_a child of this term when the entire shape of the object is known.

name: concave 3-D shape
definition: A complete three dimensional shape in which there is a line connecting pair of points on the object that lies outside the object. Or: a shape with cavities. Contrast: concave.

name: branchiness
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the degree to which there are subdivisions or offshoots in a bearer entity.

name: looseness
definition: A texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's bing full of small openings or gaps.

name: neoplastic
definition: A structural quality which is held by a bearer when the latter's disposition the presence of abnormally proliferating masses of cells.

name: coating
definition: A texture quality that exists through a liquid cover on the surface of the bearer.

name: fasciculation
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer forms a bundle of anatomical fibers, as of muscle or nerve.

name: structure, cavities
definition: A structural quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing hollow areas.

name: aplastic growth
definition: A growth quality of occurrent in which the growth of an organism, structure or group of organisms does not occur.

name: pale pink
definition: Pink color having high brightness and low saturation.

name: conical
definition: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a cone (a 3-D shape with a round cross section that tapers).

name: villiform
definition: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a minute projection (villus).

name: apical-basal polarity
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's location of features or characteristics along an apical-basal axis.

name: anterior-posterior polarity
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's location of features or characteristics along the anterior-posterior axis.

name: external angle
definition: A convex angle that is formed by one side of a polygon and a line extended from an adjacent side.

name: non-progressive
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not increasing over time.

name: osmolality
definition: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of osmoles of solute per kilogram of solvent.

name: decreased osmolality
definition: An osmolality which is relatively low.

name: increased osmolality
definition: An osmolality which is relatively high.

name: specificity to
definition: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability of a probe to react precisely with a specific target molecule.

name: upturned
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved or tilted such that the tip points upwards.

name: forward scatter
definition: A reflectivity quality inhering in light by virtue of the bearer's scattering occurring at small angle to the incident beam.

name: side scatter
definition: A reflective quality that is the light scattering occurring at wide angle (around 90 degrees) to the incident beam.

name: undivided
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being unseparated into parts or divisions.

name: ipsilateral to
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being on the same side in relation to another structure.

name: axial to
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located towards the central axis of the organism or an extremity.

name: degeneration
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer exhibiting deterioration of its structure.

name: non-degenerate
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer whose structure which does not deteriorate.

name: biconcave
definition: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's curving inward on both sides or surfaces.

name: biconvex
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being convex on both sides or surface.

name: anterior-posterior diameter
definition: A diameter that is along the anterior-posterior axis.

name: decreased anterior-posterior diameter
definition: An anterior-posterior diameter quality which is relatively small.

name: increased anterior-posterior diameter
definition: An anterior-posterior diameter quality which is relatively large.

name: trapezoid
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being a quadrilateral with two parallel sides.

name: dendritic
definition: A branched quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having smaller branches arising from larger branches. Resembling a tree in branching structure.

name: abaxial to
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being away from or on the opposite side of the central axis.

name: adaxial to
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located on the side nearest to the axis of an organ or organism.

name: mosaicism
definition: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having two or more cell populations that differ in genetic makeup. This situation can affect any type of cell, including blood cells, gametes (egg and sperm cells), and skin.

name: lateral and rotional curvature
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved around an axis and towards the side.

name: present in normal numbers in organism
definition: An amount which normal.

name: increased occurrence
definition: An occurrence which is relatively high.

name: decreased occurrence
definition: An occurrence which is relatively low.

name: dorso-ventrally flattened
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being flattened along dorso-ventral axis.

name: laterally compressed
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being flattened along transverse axis.

name: increased fragility
definition: A fragility which is relatively high.

name: decreased fragility
definition: A fragility which is relatively low.

name: increased area
definition: An area which is relatively high.

name: decreased area
definition: An area which is relatively low.

name: emmision wavelength
definition: The specific wavelength of light emitted by a fluorescent molecule, such as a labelled probe, upon absorption of light at the (higher) excitation wavelength.

name: absorption wavelength
definition: The specific wavelength of radiation that can be retained by a bearer.

name: columnar
definition: A shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being elongated and cylindrical.

name: fenestrated
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's delimited by a surface with holes.

name: star shaped
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being arranged like rays or radii; radiating from a common center.

name: crystal configuration
definition: A solid configuration inhering in a material entity by virtue of its constituent atoms, molecules, or ions being arranged in an orderly repeating pattern extending in all three spatial dimensions.

name: stratification
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's layered configuration.

name: stratified
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a layered configuration.

name: unstratified
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking a layered configuration.

name: affinity
definition: A molecular quality that arises from the molecular attraction exerted between two atoms or compounds.

name: increased affinity
definition: An affinity which is relatively high.

name: decreased affinity
definition: An affinity which is relatively low.

name: avidity
definition: A molecular quality that arises from the synergistic strength of bond affinities between multiple bond interactions.

name: increased avidity
definition: An avidity which is relatively high.

name: decreased avidity
definition: An avidity which is relatively low.

name: movement behavioral quality
definition: A behavioral quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's movement.

name: stacked
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being positioned with multiple entities of the same type above and below.

name: hollow
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an empty space or cavity within.

name: broken into two pieces
definition: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being seperated into two contiguous wholes.

name: shattered
definition: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being broken into multiple contiguous wholes.

name: partially broken
definition: A broken quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being still one contiguous whole but structurally damaged such that in danger of become two or more.

name: altered number of
definition: Having extra or fewer parts.

comment: Terms were requested by the OBI consortium but it was later decided that the term was not reflecting a quality rather what it might be refered to as a \"conferred quality\".
name: post-mortem
definition: The period after death of the organism.

comment: Terms were requested by the OBI consortium but it was later decided that the term was not reflecting a quality rather what it might be refered to as a \"conferred quality\".
name: pre-mortem
definition: The period before death of the organism.

name: bullet-shaped
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being short and wide and tapered distally.

name: monocystic
definition: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's body consisting of one sac.

name: polycystic
definition: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's body containing more than one cyst - formations of an epithelium bounded cavity not associated with neoplasia.

name: adenomatous
definition: A morphology quality inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer's exhbiting the morphological characteristics of a glandular epithelial cell.

name: subacute
definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an onset and time course between acute and chronic.

name: anaplastic
definition: A morphology quality inhering in a neoplastic cell by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting breakdown of cell-cell interaction maintaining tissue architecture, proliferative dysregulation and bizarre modification to nucleus size and shape.

name: ballooning
definition: A volume quality inhering in a degenerating cell by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting an increase in volume associated with cytoplasmic abnormalities.

name: basophilic
definition: An affinity inhering in a tissue constituent by virtue of the bearer exhibiting a molecular interaction for basic dyes under specific ph conditions.

name: neoplasm disposition
definition: A disposition inhering in a tumour to progress or fail to progress during it's life time.

name: neoplastic, non-malignant
definition: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer's disposition not to progress, invade surrounding tissues or metastasize.

name: neoplastic, malignant
definition: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer's disposition to progress, invade surrounding tissues or metastasize.

name: neoplastic, metastatic
definition: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer's disposition to spread and invade distant tissues.

name: differentiated
definition: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its stable specialization to a particular cell type.

name: undifferentiated
definition: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having not yet acquired a special structure of function.

name: metaplastic
definition: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of having changed from one fully differentiated state into another.

name: proliferative
definition: A cellular quality inhering in a cell that arises by virtue of whether the bearer exhibits the ability to grow and proliferate in number through cell division.

name: infiltrative
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's penetrating or permeating another substance or area.

name: inflammatory
definition: A compositional quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's infiltration by leukocytes, local edema and accumulation of plasma proteins.

name: hemorrhagic
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting excessive discharge of blood from the blood vessels.

name: poorly differentiated
definition: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its lacking most of the cellular characteristics which would allow it to be fully differentiated.

name: peripheral
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being at the edge or boundary of a related entity.

name: papillary
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling small nipple like projection.

name: caseous
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling cheese.

name: well differentiated
definition: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its having most of the cellular characteristics of the tissue of origin.

name: moderately well differentiated
definition: A cellular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its lacking few of the cellular characteristics which would allow it to be fully differentiated.

name: perforate
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a hole or holes, especially a row or array of small holes.

name: cribriform
definition: Perforated like a sieve.

name: fatty
definition: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing excess lipid.

name: fibrinoid
definition: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing fibrin.

name: fibrinopurulent
definition: A composition quality inhering in exudate by virtue of the bearer's containing fibrin.

name: glandular
definition: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhbiting the morphological characteristics of a gland.

name: multiple
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being present in more than two copies.

name: hydropic
definition: A structural quality which is held by a bearer when the latter exhibits an excessive accumulation of intracellular fluid.

name: suppurative
definition: A quality inhering a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to generate pus.

name: trabecular
definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's structureresembling an irregular meshwork with cross-linking struts.

name: mixed
definition: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being composed of more than one identifiable entities.

name: minimal
definition: Being smallest in amount, extent or degree.

name: laminar
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's processing the form of a thin plate sheet or layer.

name: nodular
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's consisting a knot-like mass.

name: osseous
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing bone.

name: scirrhous
definition: A hardness quality of being rigid and resistant to pressure and fibrous.

name: serous
definition: A quality inhering a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing or resembling serum.

name: neoplastic, invasive
definition: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer's disposition to invade surrounding tissues.

name: neoplastic, deeply invasive
definition: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer's disposition to invade surrounding tissues to a large extend.

name: abduction
definition: A displaced angular placement quality inhering in a body part by virtue of the bearer's movement away from the medial plane of the body.

name: neoplastic, non-invasive
definition: A disposition inhering in a tumour by virtue of the bearer's disposition not to invade surrounding tissues.

name: adduction
definition: A displaced angular placement quality inhering in a body part by virtue of the bearer's movement closer the medial plane of the body.

name: fibrillary
definition: A composition quaity inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing of or pertaining to fibrils, or nanoscale fibers.

name: delayed closure
definition: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's delay to complete the closure of the opening of an anatomical entity.

name: radiopacity
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's relative inability of electromagnetism to pass through a particular material, particularly X-rays.

name: radiopaque
definition: A readiopacity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's prevention of the passage of electromagnetic radiation.

name: edibility
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being fit to be eaten.

name: edible
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being suitable for use as food.

name: inedible
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not being suitable for use as food.

name: irregular density
definition: A density quality which lacks pattern.

name: increased radiopacity
definition: A radiopacity that is relatively high.

name: decreased radiopacity
definition: A radiopacity that is relatively low.

name: virulence
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's pathogenicity.

name: reduced virulence
definition: A virulence that is relatively low.

name: increased virulence
definition: A virulence that is relatively high.

name: ivory
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer exhibiting increased density resulting in exhibiting increased degree of radiopacity (in X-rays).

name: splayed caudal
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved outwards from the part of the body from which the tail arises.

name: splayed dorsal
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved outwards from the back or upper surface of an organism.

name: splayed lateral
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved outwards from the side.

name: splayed rostral
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved outwards the front of an organism.

name: splayed ventral
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved outwards the abdomen of an organism.

name: medially rotated
definition: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the middle of an organism.

name: laterally rotated
definition: A rotation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of being rotated towards the side of an organism.

name: partially dislocated
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being slightly out of its usual or proper place, or position.

name: bicornuate
definition: Having two horns or horn-shaped branches.

name: high-arched
definition: A concave quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's forming or resembling an arch of an increased apical height.

name: herniated into
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's bodily structure that has protruded through an abnormal opening in the wall that contains it into the surface or boundary of another entity.

name: curved medial
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved towards the middle.

name: drooping
definition: To bent or hang downwards.

name: premature closure
definition: A duration quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's premature completion of the closure of the opening of an anatomical entity.

name: herniated out of
definition: A protruding quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's bodily structure that has protruded out of the surface or boundary of another entity.

name: displaced to
definition: An angular placement quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer being changed in position in relation to another entity.

name: split medially
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being split along the median axis.

name: split laterally
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being split asymmetrically on one side.

name: split bilaterally
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being split on two side.

name: split radially
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being split along the radial axis.

name: misaligned towards
definition: An alignment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being in a improper spatial positioning towards an additional entity.

name: misaligned away from
definition: An alignment quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being in a improper spatial positioning away from an additional entity.

name: deviation
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's changed direction of position towards another entity.

name: deviation towards the lateral side
definition: A deviation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's changed direction of position towards the side.

name: deviation towards the medial side
definition: A deviation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's changed direction of position towards the middle.

name: mislocalised radially
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being out of its usual or proper place, or position around a central point or axis.

name: mislocalised proximally
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being positioned towards to point of attachment or origin.

name: straight
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being free of curves, bends, or angles.

name: displaced
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer's being changed in position.

name: molecular quality
definition: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity, a single molecule, atom, ion, radical etc.

name: cyclicity
definition: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of whether that there is a presence of cycles in the connection of the atoms within the molecular entity.

name: cyclic cyclicity
definition: Cyclic cyclicity inheres in a molecule when the atoms of the molecule do contain at least one cycle in the atom-atom connection paths (through bonds).

name: acyclic cyclicity
definition: Acyclic cyclicity inheres in a molecule when the atoms within the molecule do not contain at least one cycle in the atom-atom connection paths (through the bonds).

name: polarity
definition: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of whether or not the molecular entity has a separation of electric charge which leads to the molecule having an electric dipole.

name: polar polarity
definition: Polar polarity is a quality that inheres in a molecular entity when the molecular entity is polar, i.e. does possess an electric dipole.

name: nonpolar polarity
definition: A molecular quality which inheres in a molecular entity when the molecular entity does not possess an electrical dipole.

name: electric polarizability
definition: The ease of distortion of the electron cloud of a molecular entity by an electric field.

name: aromaticity
definition: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the presence of a conjugated ring of unsaturated bonds, lone pairs, or empty orbitals that exhibit a stabilization stronger than would be expected by the stabilization of conjugation alone.

name: aromatic
definition: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity when it possesses at least one ring that is aromatic, i.e. A conjugated ring of unsaturated bonds, lone pairs, or empty orbitals that exhibit a stabilization stronger than would be expected by the stabilization of conjugation alone.

name: non-aromatic
definition: A quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecule possessing no rings that are aromatic.

name: electric charge
definition: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the overall electric charge of the molecule, which is due to a comparison between the total number of electrons and the total number of protons.

name: neutral charge
definition: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecular entity possessing the same amount of electrons overall as protons, thus having an overall neutral charge.

name: positive charge
definition: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecular entity possessing more protons overall than electrons, thus having an overall positive charge.

name: negative charge
definition: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the molecular entity possessing more electrons overall than protons, thus having an overall negative charge.

name: electronegativity
definition: A quality that describes the power of an atom to attract electrons to itself .

name: quality of a substance
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

name: meltability
definition: A quality which inheres in a substance by virtue of the ease with which the substance can be changed from a solid to a liquid state especially by the application of heat.

name: vaporizability
definition: A quality which inheres in a substance by virtue of the ease with which the substance can be changed into a gaseous state.

comment: Adapted from Wikipedia and the birnlex term that is dbxref'd. Added on behalf of OBI at March 2010 workshop.
name: handedness
definition: A behavioral quality inhering ina bearer by virtue of the bearer's unequal distribution of fine motor skill between its left and right hands or feet.

name: left handedness
definition: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the left hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

name: right handedness
definition: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the right hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

name: ambidextrous handedness
definition: Handedness where the organism exhibits no overall dominance in the use of right or left hand or foot in the performance of tasks that require one hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

comment: Capacitance is also a measure of the amount of electrical energy stored (or separated) for a given electric potential.
name: capacitance
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to hold an electrical charge.

name: neonatal
definition: A maturity quality inhering to a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being at the point or short after birth.

name: insertion depth
definition: A quality that is the distance between the end of the inserted object and the surface of the object into which it penetrates.

name: spoon-shaped
definition: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being shaped in the form of a spoon.

name: incisiform
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having the shape of an incisor tooth.

name: bulbous
definition: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a teardrop.

name: recurved
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved backward or inward.

name: slender
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being small or narrow in circumference or width in proportion to length or height.

name: obclavate
definition: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's shape being inversely clavate.

name: bilobed
definition: A lobed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being divided into or having two lobes.

name: falciform
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having the shape of a scythe or sickle.

name: ubiquinated
definition: A molecular quality that pertains to the post-translational modification of a protein by the covalent attachment of one or more ubiquitin monomer.

name: nitrated
definition: A molecular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being combined, or impregnated, with nitric acid, or some of its compounds.

comment: For example loss of myelin sheath from a normally myelinated axon or dendrite.
name: demyelinated
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's loss of myelin sheath.

name: fan-shaped
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer that is shaped in the form of a fan.

name: phosphorylated
definition: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the bearer's having a phosphate (PO4) group.

name: increased phosphorylation
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being phosphorylated to a more than normal extent, or fully saturated with phosphate groups.

name: decreased phosphorylation
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being phosphorylated to a lesser than normal extent, or less than fully.

name: oxidized
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having reacted with oxygen, or been modified by oxidation (the reaction in which the atoms of an element lose electrons and the valence of the element increases).

name: V-shaped
definition: An angular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a single angle in its length giving the bearer the form of the letter V.

name: L-shaped
definition: An angular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a single angle in its length giving the bearer the form of the letter L.

name: subcylindrical
definition: A cylindrical shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being imperfectly cylindrical or approximately cylindrical.

name: cup-shaped
definition: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's shape form resembling the shape of a cup.

name: acuminate
definition: A tapered shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's tapering gradually to a sharp point.

name: subrectangular
definition: A quadrangular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being approximately rectangular.

name: subtriangular
definition: A triangular shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being nearly, but not perfectly, triangular.

name: multifid
definition: A split shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having or being divided into many lobes or similar segments.

name: semicircular
definition: A 2-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having shape or form of half a circle.

name: far from
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located far (not close to) in space in relation to another entity.

name: emarginate
definition: A notched shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a notched tip or edge.

name: blade-like
definition: A tapered shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being flat, slender, and tapering to a point.

name: aliform
definition: Shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being shaped like a wing.

name: retrorse
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved backward or downward.

name: antrorse
definition: A curvature quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being curved forward or upward.

name: hourglass-shaped
definition: A concave 3-D shape that inheres in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's nearly) symmetric shape wide at its ends and narrow in the middle, resembling the figure of number 8.

name: teardrop-shaped
definition: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's shape resembling falling drop.

name: trilobed
definition: A lobed quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being divided into or having three lobes.

name: velocity
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's rate of change of the position.

name: fluid flow rate
definition: A physical quality inhering in a fluid (liquid or gas) by virtue of the amount of fluid which passes through a given surface per unit time.

name: mass flow rate
definition: A flow rate quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the mass of substance which passes through a given surface per unit time.

name: increased force
definition: A force which relative high.

name: decreased force
definition: A force which is relative low.

name: degree of pigmentation
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having or lacking of substances produced by living organisms that have a color resulting from selective color absorption.

name: pigmented
definition: A degree of pigmentation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having substances produced by living organisms that have a color resulting from selective color absorption.

name: unpigmented
definition: A degree of pigmentation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking substances produced by living organisms that have a color resulting from selective color absorption.

name: increased pigmentation
definition: A degree of pigmentation quality that is relative high.

name: decreased pigmentation
definition: A degree of pigmentation quality that is relative low.

name: antero-posteriorly flattened
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being flattened along the antero-posterior axis.

name: platelike
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being roundish, flattish shape, possibly with a slightly angled edge.

comment: Becoming flat but not necessarily completely flat.
name: flattened
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's surface becoming more extended in a plane.

name: grooved
definition: Texture quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked with one or more channels.

name: tricuspidate
definition: A cuscpidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing three cusps.

name: multicuspidate
definition: A cuscpidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing more than one cusp.

name: pointed
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a point.

name: adjacent to
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located near in space in relation to another entity.

name: semi erect
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being partially upright in position or posture.

name: located in
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's location within another entity.

name: phosphorylation
definition: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the addition of a phosphate (PO4) group to the bearer.

name: dephosphorylated
definition: A quality inhering in a protein or a molecule by virtue of the bearer's lacking a phosphate (PO4) group.

name: organization quality
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being arranged in a systematic fashion.

name: behavioural activity
definition: A behavioral quality of a process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to exhibit marked activity.

name: 3-D shape
definition: A shape that inheres in a 3 dimensional entity.

name: centered
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located in a position equidistant from edges.

name: accumulation
definition: A structural quality of the collection or massing of one physical object within another physical object.

name: increased accumulation
definition: An increased number of physical objects that are accumulated within another physical object usually as a result of a failure to break down or remove objects in a timely manner.

name: decreased accumulation
definition: An accumulation which is relative low.

name: parallel to
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located at the same continuous distance relative to another object.

name: marbled
definition: Multicolored quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being colored with a variegated pattern resembling marble,.

name: mottled
definition: Multicolored quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being dappled with spots, patches, or blotches of different colors.

name: high contrast color pattern
definition: A color pattern quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's color pattern in which light and dark colors (for example white and black) are codistributed to create a visual impression.

name: barred
definition: A color pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of bearer's exhibiting vertical bars of one hue or degree of saturation crossing another.

name: iridescent
definition: A quality of certain surfaces which appear to change colour as the angle of view changes.

name: articulated with
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's participating in a joint with another entity.

name: tightly articulated with
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being strongly articulated with another entity.

name: broadly articulated with
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's possessing a broad surface in articulation with another entity.

name: biscupidate
definition: A cuscpidate quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer possessing two cusps.

name: increased mobility
definition: A mobility which is relative high.

name: decreased mobility
definition: A mobility which is relative low.

name: tension
definition: A physical quality that pertains by virtue of a pulling force that is directed away from the bearer and attempts to stretch or elongate the bearer.

name: increased branchiness
definition: Branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of increasing the degree to which there are subdivisions or offshoots in a bearer entity.

name: decreased branchiness
definition: Branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of decreasing the degree to which there are subdivisions or offshoots in a bearer entity.

name: increased elasticity
definition: An elasticity which is relatively high.

name: decreased elasticity
definition: An elasticity which is relatively low.

comment: Setose as a label is used extensively to describe insect phenotypes that have hairy-like appearances (i.e., they are covered in setae, not the hairs of mammals). A bristle is a type of seta.
name: setose
definition: A hairy quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being covered with setae.

name: agenesis
definition: Failure of a tissue of organ to develop.

comment: For example, structures undergoing endochondral ossification change in composition from cartilaginous to ossified.
name: transient
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's underlying structure being capable of change.

name: permanent
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's underlying structure not changing over time.

name: scrobiculate
definition: A texture that is uniformly covered in short, oblong, or trench-like depressions.

name: areolate
definition: A surface feature shape inhering in a surface by virtue of the bearer's being divided by ridge-like structures into a number of small, irregular spaces.

name: foveate
definition: A texture quality inhering in a surface by virtue of the bearer's being marked by the presence of small, shallow, regular depressions called fovae.

name: decreased cellular motility
definition: A cellular motility which is lower relative to the normal or average.

name: increased cellular motility
definition: A cellular motility which is higher relative to the normal or average.

name: tubular
definition: A cylindrical shape that is hollow.

name: increased quality
definition: A quality that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

name: decreased quality
definition: A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

name: decreased process quality
definition: A quality of a process that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

name: decreased object quality
definition: A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

name: increased process quality
definition: A quality of a process that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

name: increased object quality
definition: A quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

name: equilateral triangular
definition: A triangular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having all sides of the same length.

name: isosceles triangular
definition: A triangular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having two sides have the same length.

name: scalene triangular
definition: A triangular quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having all sides of unequal length.

comment: Note that a fiber shaped object may take any circuitous or straight path through space (think of a length of string or rope).
name: fiber shaped
definition: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a consistently sized and approximately round cross-section along its length, which is many times larger than its diameter.

name: robust
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being strong, thick or sturdy.

name: fimbriated
definition: Having a fringe or border of hairlike or fingerlike projections.

name: segmented
definition: Consisting of segments or similar parts arranged in a longitudinal series.

name: telescopic
definition: Having or resembling the shape of a telescope.

name: ligamentous
definition: Having the nature or characteristic of, a ligament; composed of the tissue proper to ligaments.

name: brush-like shape
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling the end of a brush with a multitude of bristles.

name: autogenous
definition: Being separate or discrete from other skeletal elements.

name: parallelogram
definition: A convex quadrilateral is a parallelogram if and only if any one of the following statements are true:\\n1. Each diagonal divides the quadrilateral into two congruent triangles with the same orientation.\\n2. The opposite sides are congruent in pairs.\\n3. The diagonals bisect each other.\\n4. The opposite angles are congruent in pairs.\\n5. The sum of the squares of the sides equals the sum of the squares of the diagonals. (This is the parallelogram law)\\n6.It possesses rotational symmetry.\\n7.One pair of opposite sides are parallel and congruent.\\n8.Two pairs of adjacent angles are supplementary.

name: superelliptic
definition: A shape constituting a transition between a rectangle and a circle; a closed curve, of which the circle and ellipse are special cases, whose parametric equation is x = a.cos2/rt, y = b.cos2/rt

name: squircle
definition: A shape with properties between those of a square and those of a circle.

name: diamond shaped
definition: A superelptic shape inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's shape resembling a diamond.

name: temporal distribution quality
definition: A temporal distribution pattern of process occurrences within a regulation/reference process.

name: offset quality
definition: The temporal relation between the end of the process with respect to a reference process.

name: onset quality
definition: The temporal relation between the start of the process with respect to a reference process.

name: angle
definition: An orientation inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement at an angle.

name: increased angle to
definition: An angle which is relatively high.

name: decreased angle to
definition: An angle which is relatively low.

name: hyponastic
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a upward bending of its leaves or other plant parts.

name: oblanceolate
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being extended along a straight line, and is shaped like a reversed lance-point, with the tapering point attached to the leafstalk.

name: adhesive
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer exhibiting molecular attraction to another entity in contact.

name: non-adhesive
definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer not exhibiting molecular attraction to another entity in contact.

name: increased adhesivity
definition: A adhesivity which is relatively high.

name: decreased adhesivity
definition: A adhesivity which is relatively low.

name: tholiform
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being dome-shaped.

name: pyramidal
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having triangular faces that meet at a common point and containing a polygonal shaped base.

name: lance-ovate
definition: A spheroid quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a continuous convex surface with an axis of symmetry and one axis longer than the other; characterized with an egg-shaped form crossed with a lance-head shaped form.

name: lanceolate-triangular
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being shaped like a lance-head, considerably longer than wide, tapering towards the tip from below the middle together forming three angles; attached at the broad end.

name: hispid
definition: A quality of being covered with stiff or rough hairs.

name: hispidulous
definition: A quality of being minutely hispid.

name: tomentose
definition: A quality of being covered with short, dense, matted hairs.

name: cupulate
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being a cupule, with a structure similar to a cup that also encloses the ovule in partiality.

name: decumbent
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lying or growing on the ground but with erect or rising tips.

name: arachnose
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being characterized by fine, entangled hairs giving the appearance of cobweb.

name: lemon-shaped
definition: A convex 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a quadric surface in three dimensions obtained by rotating less than half of a circular arc about an axis passing through the endpoints of the arc

name: snowman-shaped
definition: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having two connected parts, roughly spherical, of different sizes.

name: obconical
definition: A conical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resembling a cone, with the pointed end attached to an organism.

name: ligneous
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer resembling wood.

name: basal to
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located toward the base of an organism relative to another entity.

name: cauline to
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located toward the stalk of an organism relative to another entity.

name: fleshy
definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer resembling or containing flesh.

name: herbaceous
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's upper parts die back to the rootstock at the end of the growing season.

name: activation quality
definition: A quality that inheres in a bearer in virtue of its realizing one of its functions.

name: active
definition: A quality of an physical object that is currently realizing one of its functions.

name: inactive
definition: A quality of a physical object that is currently realizing none of its functions.

name: constitutively active
definition: A quality of a physical object that has been constantly realizing some of its functions.

name: D-shaped
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a strait side and an arched side giving the bearer the form of the letter D.

name: ridged
definition: An elongated raised margin or border.

name: broad
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's width being notably higher than its length.

name: tendency
definition: A disposition that can be compared on a linear scale - that is that it can be increased or decreased.

name: increased tendency
definition: A tendency which is relatively high.

name: decreased tendency
definition: A tendency which is relatively low.

name: bronze
definition: A medium brown color with a metallic sheen, resembles the actual alloy bronze.

name: shortened
definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's length being notably lower than its width.

name: intact female
definition: Female quality of having complete, unaltered reproductive organs

name: intact male
definition: Male quality of having complete, unaltered reproductive organs.

name: castrated male
definition: Male quality of being incapable to reproduce because of functional loss of the testicles from surgical removal or chemical means.

name: nulliparous
definition: A viviparous organism having never given birth.

name: multiparous
definition: A viviparous organism that has given birth two or more times.

name: parity
definition: The number of time that a viviparous organism has given birth.

name: primiparous
definition: A viviparous organism having given birth one time.

name: grand multi[arous
definition: A viviparous organism that has given birth five or more times.

name: mediolateral polarity
definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's location of features or characteristics along the mediolateral axis.

name: fluctuating
definition: Recurrent and often more or less cyclic alteration.

name: trumpet-shaped
definition: A concave 3-D shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's shape form resembling the shape of a trumpet.

name: inflated
definition: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being filled with air.

name: uninflated
definition: A structure quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being not filed with air.

name: acinus
definition: Having a shape that resembles a many-lobed \\\"berry,\\\" such as a raspberry.

name: ovariohysterectomized female
definition: A female fertility quality inhering in a female by virtue of the bearer's not being capable of reproducing because of surgical removal of ovaries and uterus.

name: ovariectomized female
definition: A female fertility quality inhering in a female by virtue of the bearer's not being capable of reproducing because of surgical removal of ovaries.

name: waxiness
definition: A composition quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the presence of long chain aliphatic lipids on the surface of an organism.

name: increased waxiness
definition: A waxiness which is relatively high.

name: decreased waxiness
definition: A waxiness which is relatively low.

name: waxy
definition: Presence of long chain aliphatic lipids on the surface of an organism.

name: striate-angular
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being marked by narrow lines, usually parallel, with at least one salient angle on the margin

name: anvil
